27/12/2010
VIENNA, Austria -- Former Croatian Prime Minister Ivo Sanader is expected to appear on Monday (December 27th) before an Austrian judge to say whether he accepts a simplified process for his extradition. 
Sanader was arrested on December 10th in Salzburg based on an international arrest warrant issued by Croatia, where he is being investigated for possible criminal actions and abuse of power. 
A day after his arrest, a judge in Salzburg ordered him held for 14 days, pending extradition. 
(HRT, Nova TV, Tanjug - 26/12/10)
